{"questionId":"32388549-e820-4b4a-91a9-d9c32e611098_5","correctAnswer":"A","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Set up","content":"Start with $p = \\sqrt{12c} - 25$. Add 25 to both sides: $p + 25 = \\sqrt{12c}$."},{"title":"Solve","content":"Square both sides: $(p+25)^2 = 12c$. Divide by 12: $c = \\dfrac{(p+25)^2}{12}$."},{"title":"Answer","content":"<strong>A</strong> is correct."}]}